    "While there she worked with the early American Duchamp curator <a href=\"/hoppsw\">Walter C. Hopps</a>.": [],
    "She moved to the Art Institute of Chicago in 1969 as curator of 20th-century art at the Art Institute of Chicago.": [],
    "At Chicago, she met assistant curator of European painting, <a href=\"/rishelj\">Joseph H. Rishel, Jr.</a> They married in 1971, rising to associate curator of 20th-century art at Chicago the same year.": [],
    "The following year she returned to Philadelphia as curator of 20th century art, in part to organize and mount the Marcel Duchamp a retrospective the following year, of which the Museum had spectacular holdings.": [],
